

{ The «magic» SysRq key

  The magical SysRq key is a key-combination that can be pressed when the kernel seems to be unresponsive.

  It is enabled with the → Linux/kernel/CONFIG/MAGIC_SYSRQ kernel configuration.

}
sa:

  `→ Linux/fhs/proc/sys/kernel/sysrq`,
  `→ Linux/fhs/proc/sysrq-trigger`,
  `→ Linux/kernel/source/drivers/tty/sysrq_c`,
  `→ Linux/kernel/source/Documentation/sysrq_txt`

  The SysRq key was added with on the → hardware/keyboard#keyboard-pc-at[PC/AT keyboard].
